<paragraph id="8BFD45513608D06056E4FAE4FDB84E10" blockId="2.[151,1437,1307,1873]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
Kim 
<emphasis id="B93699433608D06056A3FAE4FE334E7C" box="[208,264,1307,1333]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">et al.</emphasis>
(2008) resurrected 
<taxonomicName id="4C423ED23608D0605790FAE4FDF74E7C" authority="Girault" authorityName="Girault" authorityYear="1913" box="[483,716,1307,1333]" class="Insecta" family="Eulophidae" genus="Selitrichodes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93699433608D0605790FAE4FD4E4E7C" box="[483,629,1307,1333]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Selitrichodes</emphasis>
Girault
</taxonomicName>
from a long list of synonyms of 
<taxonomicName id="4C423ED23608D0605249FAE4FBF04E7C" authorityName="Westwood" authorityYear="1833" box="[1082,1227,1307,1333]" class="Insecta" family="Eulophidae" genus="Aprostocetus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93699433608D0605249FAE4FBF04E7C" box="[1082,1227,1307,1333]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Aprostocetus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD338A03608D0605286FAE4FAA74E7C" author="Boucek, Z." box="[1269,1436,1307,1333]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" refId="ref18491" refString="Boucek, Z. (1988) Australasian Chalcidoidea (Hymenoptera): A Biosystematic Revision of Genera of Fourteen Families, with a Reclassification of Species. CAB International, Wallingford, 832 pp." type="book" year="1988">Bouček (1988)</bibRefCitation>
and also provided a diagnosis for the genus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C35816DA3608D06056B4FA9CFC2E4C18" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BFD45513608D06056B4FA9CFED94EA0" blockId="2.[151,1437,1307,1873]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
The present species is unique and runs close to different genera (like 
<taxonomicName id="4C423ED23608D06055B9FA9CFBE14E34" authority="Westwood" authorityName="Westwood" authorityYear="1833" box="[970,1242,1379,1405]" class="Insecta" family="Eulophidae" genus="Aprostocetus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93699433608D06055B9FA9CFB604E34" box="[970,1115,1379,1405]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Aprostocetus</emphasis>
Westwood
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C423ED23608D0605297FA9CFA554E34" box="[1252,1390,1379,1405]" class="Insecta" family="Eulophidae" genus="Oncastichus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93699433608D0605297FA9CFA554E34" box="[1252,1390,1379,1405]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Oncastichus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
LaSalle and 
<taxonomicName id="4C423ED23608D0605774FA78FED44EE8" authority="Foerster" authorityName="Foerster" box="[263,495,1415,1441]" class="Insecta" family="Eulophidae" genus="Baryscapus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93699433608D0605774FA78FEB14EE9" box="[263,394,1415,1440]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Baryscapus</emphasis>
Foerster
</taxonomicName>
) in generic keys by different workers, as discussed under the comments. It has also been compared with other related gall forming genera such as 
<taxonomicName id="4C423ED23608D060552AFA54FB5C4E8C" authority="Kim &amp; La Salle" authorityName="Kim &amp; La Salle" authorityYear="2005" box="[857,1127,1451,1477]" class="Insecta" family="Eulophidae" genus="Moona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93699433608D060552AFA54FC934E8D" box="[857,936,1451,1476]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Moona</emphasis>
Kim &amp; La Salle
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C423ED23608D0605200FA54FAA74E8C" authority="Girault" authorityName="Girault" authorityYear="1913" box="[1139,1436,1451,1477]" class="Insecta" family="Eulophidae" genus="Quadrastichodella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93699433608D0605200FA54FA7E4E8C" box="[1139,1349,1451,1477]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Quadrastichodella</emphasis>
Girault
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C423ED23608D06056B4FA30FED94EA0" authority="Kim &amp; La Salle." box="[199,482,1487,1513]" class="Insecta" family="Eulophidae" genus="Leprosa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93699433608D06056B4FA30FE194EA1" box="[199,290,1487,1512]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Leprosa</emphasis>
Kim &amp; La Salle.
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFD45513608D06056B4FA0CFB4B4D1C" blockId="2.[151,1437,1307,1873]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
According to the diagnosis by Kim 
<emphasis id="B93699433608D0605429FA0CFDB74D44" box="[602,652,1523,1549]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">et al</emphasis>
. (2008) the present species can be accommodated fairly well in 
<taxonomicName id="4C423ED23608D0605312FA0CFFCC4D78" authorityName="Girault" authorityYear="1913" class="Insecta" family="Eulophidae" genus="Selitrichodes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93699433608D0605312FA0CFFCC4D78" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Selitrichodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, except for the character ‘3–5 dorsal setae on SMV’ instead of usually having between 1–3. Another species— 
<taxonomicName id="4C423ED23608D06056ACF9C4FD7F4D1C" authority="Fisher &amp; La Salle" authorityName="Fisher &amp; La Salle" authorityYear="2014" box="[223,580,1595,1621]" class="Insecta" family="Eulophidae" genus="Selitrichodes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="casuarinae">
<emphasis id="B93699433608D06056ACF9C4FFD64D1C" box="[223,237,1595,1621]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B93699433608D0605688F9C4FE4C4D1D" box="[251,375,1595,1620]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">casuarinae</emphasis>
Fisher &amp; La Salle
</taxonomicName>
also differs in this character by having 3–4 setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFD45513608D06056B4F9A0FC2E4C18" blockId="2.[151,1437,1307,1873]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
